			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Background</strong><br />
Cignifi is looking for a highly motivated, organized, Product Manager with excellent oral and written communication skills. You&rsquo;ll be responsible for developing proposals, setting implementation goals, reviewing launch results, and ensuring success for our customers.</p>
<p>
You will have the option to be based at the Company&rsquo;s head office in Cambridge, MA or co-located with its development team in San Francisco, with unique opportunities to spend time with customers and our local teams in Brazil, Mexico and elsewhere.</p>
<p>
You should expect to be challenged with complex problems and be deeply engaged with the company&rsquo;s clients and with Cignifi&rsquo;s senior management team.</p>
<p>
Here are some <em>areas you&rsquo;d be working on</em>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Collaborating with our head of products to build rich product requirements for our development team</li>
<li>
Developing implementation plans to deploy Cignifi&rsquo;s decision and scoring platform with customers</li>
<li>
Designing testing strategies to demonstrate the ROI of Cignifi&rsquo;s models compared to existing customer platforms and scores</li>
<li>
Design and implement systems to evaluate test outcomes, determine score adjustments, strategy changes, or follow-on test plans</li>
<li>
Collect and compile feedback from customers to drive product development and innovation</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>You should have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Exposure to products with complex sales cycles (e.g. decision platforms, campaign management tools, analytics, enterprise systems&hellip;)</li>
<li>
Some experience working with large datasets, preferably commercial in nature (telecom, financial, retail, media, online advertising, social media&hellip;.)</li>
<li>
Familiarity with the basics of consumer credit, A/B testing strategies</li>
<li>
A data-driven attitude towards everything you do</li>
<li>
Bonus for familiarity prototyping in Axure, Balsamiq, Photoshop or other tools</li>
<li>
Familiarity with building custom reports in Business Intelligence tools</li>
<li>
Comfortable working in a small, intense and high-growth start-up environment</li>
<li>
Excellent interpersonal and presentational skills</li>
</ul>
<p>
<em>Compensation</em><br />
Compensation will comprise base salary, bonus, and stock option plan.<br />
Compensation will be competitive to attract the best talent.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
